'''Chronometry''' (from [[Ancient Greek|Greek]] χρόνος ''[[chronos]]'', "time" and μέτρον ''metron'', "measure") is the science of the measurement of [[time]], or timekeeping.<ref>''Webster's Dictionary'', 1913</ref> Chronometry applies to [[electronics|electronic]] devices, while [[horology]] refers to mechanical devices.

It should not to be confused with [[chronology]], the science of locating events in time, which often relies upon it.

